[InvalidElementStateException](https://www.selenium.dev/selenium/docs/api/java/org/openqa/selenium/InvalidElementStateException.html) implies that a WebElement is in a certain state when actions cannot be performed with it. One of the most frequently encountered examples would include an element being obscured by another when clicking, or perhaps not being visible on the [HTML DOM](https://www.w3schools.com/js/js_htmldom.asp).


